  "prompt": "I know the basics of English and I can speak it normally, but I don't know about sentence structure. What can help me to know sentence structure?",
  "response": "Here are some helpful ways to improve your understanding of English sentence structure:\n\n1. Learn basic sentence components\n- Subject (who/what)\n- Verb (action)\n- Object (receiving the action)\n\n2. Study basic sentence types\n- Simple sentence\n- Compound sentence\n- Complex sentence\n- Compound-complex sentence\n\n3. Resources to help you\n- Grammar books\n- Online grammar websites\n- YouTube tutorials\n- Language learning apps (Duolingo, Babbel)\n- English grammar websites\n\n4. Practice techniques\n- Read English books\n- Watch English movies/TV shows\n- Practice writing\n- Take online grammar quizzes\n- Listen to native speakers\n\n5. Key grammar rules to focus on\n- Subject-verb agreement\n- Verb tenses\n- Sentence word order\n- Clauses and phrases\n\n6. Recommended resources\n- \"English Grammar in Use\" by Raymond Murphy\n- Grammarly website\n- Khan Academy grammar lessons\n- BBC Learning English website\n\n7. Additional tips\n- Learn one grammar rule at a time\n- Don't get overwhelmed\n- Practice consistently\n- Be patient with yourself\n\nWould you like me to recommend specific online resources or explain any of these points in more detail?",
